One right that animals should obtain is the right to roam free in their native land. Zoos, for example, confine animals and place them on display for human entertainment. This contains wild animals from living a natural life. However, some might claim that animals are safer in a zoo versus the wild. Zoos have proven helpful for breeding and decreasing extinction rate. Respectfully, animals are just as capable, and may feel more safe, breeding in the wild.

m, similar rights to humans. Animals should not be held captive in zoos, animal shelters or abusive homes. Confining them in cages and fences deprives them of a natural life.
